# run.log — ATOM-105 (clean-run readiness, kit v0.3.1)

[breath] Mandate read (ATOM-105-LAUNCH.md, canonical). G1 = INFO-035. Kit
v0.3.1, tree A, envelope ~70k. Four DoD points: language consistency,
clean slate (--uninstall), harness scenarios, compatibility. The live CEO
question — why did he see an EN финал — must be answered by CODE, not by
guess, and reported as a separate line.

[investigate] EN-финал root cause. Walked install.sh across committed
versions v0.1 (a097c59) → v0.3. Facts: (a) the --apply-update prompt was
never EN-hardcoded — L_UPDATE_ASK_CONFIRM localized since v0.1; the
mandate's install.sh:887 claim does not hold in ANY committed version;
(b) is_affirmative accepted да/da/yes since v0.1 on all paths;
(c) answer_language persisted in install-state.json and restored on
resume and in every subcommand since v0.1. The only silent-EN paths that
DID exist: (1) step_language falls back to lang="en" on EOF or after 5
unrecognized answers — with no honest line (e.g. answering «русский» in
words was unrecognized: only 3/ru matched); (2) ${ANSWER_LANGUAGE:-en} in
resolve_and_load_state when the state field is empty — also silent.
Conclusion: the CEO's install-state most probably records
answer_language=en (explicit q1 answer, or silent fallback 1).
Verifiable on his machine: grep answer_language <workdir>/install-state.json.

[build 1 — language] Both silent fallbacks made honest (trilingual line).
q1 parsing widened: english/eng, romana/română/romaneste, rus/русский/
по-русски now recognized (question text untouched — NOT-DOING respected).
