[harness-catch — REAL BUG] Scenario 15's no-op leg failed on first run:
cmd_uninstall deleted the shared WORKDIR_POINTER even when there was
nothing to uninstall — i.e. uninstalling «nothing» would orphan ANOTHER
install's pointer on a real machine. Fixed: pointer removed only when
have_state=1 AND pointer content == WORKSPACE_DIR. Re-run green. This is
the falsifiable-asserts discipline (r1-F1 lesson) paying off again.

